Utterance.UttText: In Bed 7, we have kAte orange, 41 yrs old under Dr Li, came in with fracture of the skull due to car accident and came into the ward post brain surgery a week ago and she is much better.
Her head is not swollen nor there's any sign of bleeding and it is healing normally. she is on antibiotics still and it was on IVabs yesterday and now they have started her on orals.
She is self caring with very minimal assistance. she is tolerating her diet and fluids well.
She is ambulant and walks around the ward in short distances only. her obs are all stable.
